frameDefinitions: This frame is about the static comparison of an Profiled_item to a Standard_item, often  with respect to some Attribute.
The existence of a State_of_affairs is sufficient reason for taking an Action .
This frame contains LUs that ascribe an artistic quality to a work.
An Assessor examines a Phenomenon to figure out its Value according to some Feature of the Phenomenon.
A Cognizer construes an Item as belonging to a certain Category.
Compared to its Competitors, a Standard is at the high end of a scale with respect to some Variable.
frameExamples: The Sun is putting on a show that <t>rivals</t> the most sizzling Hollywood thrillers.
The underwater sequences <t>warrant</t> the price of the admission alone.
With its lack of decor, the church seems quite <t>austere</t>.
Each company is then <t>evaluated</t> for their earning potential. CNI

listRoleDefinitions: In active sentences, the <fen>Profiled_item</fen> is the grammatically more prominent one of the items that are compared and realized as  the subject. .
In active setnnces, the <fen>Standard_item</fen> is  the grammatically less prominent element, i.e. the object or an oblique.
This Frame Elements marks constituents that indicate in which respect Item-1 and Item-2 are equal to each other.
The <fen>Standard_attribute</fen> is used when the standard is a specific value on  a scale.
The <fen>Profiled_attribute</fen> is a particular value on a scale which is being compared to a <fen>Standard_item</fen> or <fen>Profiled_attribute</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Profiled_item</fen> rivals the <fen>Standard_item</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Profiled_item</fen> rivals the <fen>Standard_item</fen>.
An Eventuality or an Entity that is taken to constitute sufficient reason for taking another <fen>Action</fen>.
An <fen>Action</fen> that is taken to be justifiable given the <fen>State_of_Affairs</fen>.
The <fen>Entity</fen> for which a particular gradable <fen>Attribute</fen> is appropriate and under consideration.
The feature of an <fen>Entity</fen> which is under discussion.
A modifier expressing the deviation of the <fen>Entity</fen> or <fen>Attribute</fen> from the norm.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> or its <fen>Attribute</fen> is in the state of having the specified style.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> has the <fen>Attribute</fen> to a given <fen>Degree</fen>.
The sentient entity that evaluates the <fen>Phenomenon</fen>.
The entity whose <fen>Value</fen> according to a <fen>Feature</fen> is being measured.
The type of property or feature that the <fen>Phenomenon</fen> is being judged on.
An event or procedure that allows the <fen>Assessor</fen> to evaluate the <fen>Phenomenon</fen>.
<fen>Medium</fen> is the physical entity or channel used by the <fen>Assessor</fen> to make the assessment.
The time at which the <fen>Assessor</fen> makes the assessment.
The location where the assessing takes place.
This is the person who performs an act of categorization. Typically, this frame element is expressed as an External Argument.
This is the entity which is construed or treated by the <fen>Cognizer</fen> as being an instance of a particular <fen>Category</fen>. Typically, the <fen>Item</fen> is expressed as an Object.

This frame element expresses a general type or class of which the <fen>Item</fen> is considered an instance. Typically, it is expressed in a prepositional phrase headed by <ment>as</ment> or <ment>under</ment>.

This frame element expresses properties of the <fen>Item</fen> which is used as a basis for categorization. <fen>Criteria</fen> are the general dimensions along which <fen>Item</fen>s can potentially differ from one another and hence, fall into different <fen>Category</fen>s. For example, a paint sample can be classified <ment>by color</ment> or <ment>by finish (matte or gloss)</ment>; if they are classified by color, one can be classified <ment>as orange</ment> and another <ment>as red</ment>. The <fen>Criteria</fen> role is typically expressed as a PP headed by <ment>by</ment>, or as a complex PP of the form <ment>on the basis of...</ment>:
This Frame Element marks expressions that indicate when a certain Categorization was made.
The <fen>Standard</fen> is the entity that is located closest to the end of the scale evoked by some <fen>Variable</fen>.
The <fen>Variable</fen> is a property that evokes a scale along which the <fen>Standard</fen> is located closest to one extreme in  comparison to its <fen>Competitors</fen>.
The role <fen>Competitors</fen> denotes the entities that are exceeded by the <fen>Standard</fen> with regard to the <fen>Variable</fen>.
